 {"id":"franken_numpy-wtko","title":"numpy.triu_indices python wrapper parity","description":"Add fnp_python.triu_indices passthrough wrapper around numpy.triu_indices(n, k=0, m=None). Returns a tuple of arrays indexing the upper triangle of an (n, m) array at offset k. Include oracle test covering: square (n=4, k=0), explicit m, positive k offset, negative k, n=1 edge, and a cross-check that triu_indices ∪ tril_indices(k=-1) covers all positions exactly once.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:16:22.797578238Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T05:15:12.765259555Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T05:15:12.765259555Z","close_reason":"Completed in existing committed implementation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
