+{"id":"franken_numpy-wu9u","title":"conformance_testing.rs harness for numpy.testing.assert_* parity","description":"fnp_python.testing exposes 8 native assert_* implementations (assert_equal, assert_almost_equal, assert_array_almost_equal, assert_array_less, assert_approx_equal, assert_string_equal, assert_allclose, assert_array_equal). Recent commits b730dc1 (2axo) and dc2fcb6 (u98f) reworked assert_string_equal — confirming the surface is alive and worth pinning. Ship tests/conformance_testing.rs in the same shape as conformance_fft.rs: pass-path cases under CompareMode::Strict (both return None) and fail-path cases under CompareMode::Error (both raise AssertionError with matching format). Acceptance: cargo test -p fnp-python --test conformance_testing passes; emits MUST/SHOULD/MAY summary line.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T09:22:32.389885012Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T10:06:36.278611895Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T10:06:36.276327437Z","close_reason":"tests/conformance_testing.rs lands; harness covers all 8 native testing.assert_* members across pass/fail branches; 16/16 MUST + 5/5 SHOULD + 2/2 MAY = 23/23 PASS. No drift surfaced — assert family is solid.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-wuhg","title":"Add signal differential parity cases for multi-axis trace/diagonal and percentile(nearest)","description":"bv --robot-triage has no ready beads beyond franken_numpy-rosd, so this is the fallback parity work. Promote the root repro behaviors in test_trace.py and test_nearest_method.rs into tracked conformance coverage by extending crates/fnp-conformance signal differential fixtures and runner to verify FrankenNumPy against NumPy semantics for: (1) ndarray.trace(axis1=0, axis2=1) on a 3-D input, (2) ndarray.diagonal(axis1=0, axis2=1) on a 3-D input, and (3) percentile(method=\"nearest\"). If the runner needs extra fixture fields, add them minimally and keep the fixture format explicit. Verify with rch-backed Cargo tests after the change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-04-15T03:53:53.515539764Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-15T04:00:09.811817075Z","closed_at":"2026-04-15T04:00:09.809730114Z","close_reason":"Added signal differential runner support for explicit percentile methods and multi-axis trace/diagonal cases, then added NumPy-derived fixtures for trace(axis1=0, axis2=1), diagonal(axis1=0, axis2=1), and percentile(method=\"nearest\"). Verified with CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 rch exec -- cargo check -p fnp-conformance --all-targets and CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 rch exec -- cargo test -p fnp-conformance core_suites_are_green -- --nocapture.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","parity","signal"]}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-wuz5","title":"PORT: numpy.linalg __all__ namespace parity","description":"Reality-check gap: numpy.linalg.__all__ has 32 public names in NumPy order, but fnp_python.linalg wires the functions/classes without setting or testing __all__. Add __all__ parity from numpy.linalg when available with a fallback list, preserve existing Rust-backed wrappers and numpy-owned LinAlgError/test re-exports, and add oracle coverage that every numpy.linalg.__all__ name is present in fnp_python.linalg with representative value/error behavior for at least matrix_norm/vector_norm/cross.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:16:21.651235526Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:23:58.278963911Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:23:58.277071898Z","close_reason":"Completed in 81f80ac","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["linalg","parity","python"]}
